cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.CL 

This paper deals with the task of predicting semantic segmentations of future frames in videos, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes an autoregressive convolutional neural network, which falls under the category of machine learning, specifically deep learning. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category. The paper also involves decision making in real-time systems, which could fall under the categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the paper deals with semantic segmentation, which is a subfield of natural language processing, and hence cs.CL (Computation and Language) could also be a possible category.
